    • Field Detail

      • JSON

        public static final java.lang.String JSON
        Defined as application/json;charset=UTF-8. When sending a JSON response back to the client, use this media type in stead of the prefab MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON. We seem to have reports that without the charset parameter, some browsers or browser versions don't interpret the response as expected.

      • serverErrorDebug

        public static javax.ws.rs.core.Response serverErrorDebug(java.lang.String message)
        Report a server error, but set the actual HTTP status to 200 (OK). By setting the HTTP status to 200, we are guaranteed that the browser treats and displays the response body in the most typical fashion. The content type of the response body is set to text/plain.
        Parameters:
        message -
        Returns:
